features: 【Processor】Unleash the potential of the ASUS Vivobook Laptop, driven by the potent AMD Ryzen 7 5800HS processor. Clocking at 2.80 GHz and surging to an impressive 4.40 GHz Max Boost, this powerhouse boasts 8 cores and 16 threads, empowered by a sizable 16 MB Cache. All of this power is wrapped in a thin and lightweight design, ensuring maximum portability without compromising performance.

【Vivid Display】Immerse yourself in a 16" HD Display that showcases a captivating 1920 x 1080 resolution. Revel in the impressive color accuracy and clarity this display offers, all while benefiting from the energy-efficient LED backlight that enhances your visual experience.

【Enhanced Performance】Elevate your laptop's capabilities with up to 40GB DDR4 RAM, a substantial upgrade that transforms multitasking and overall performance. Coupled with the potential of up to 1TB SSD storage, embrace the advantages of swifter start-up times, noiseless operation (thanks to the absence of moving parts), and reduced heat emissions and battery drain.

【Seamless Connectivity】Experience the power of WiFi 6 (802.11 ax), a flexible dual-band connectivity solution that boasts enhanced reliability through two data streams and antennas. Immerse yourself in Wi-Fi speeds that can achieve nearly 3X faster performance. Stay connected effortlessly, regardless of your location.

【Windows 11 Home Experience】Welcome to the world of Windows 11 Home, where familiar features are revitalized and new ways of connection are introduced. Rediscover the Start menu in a rejuvenated form and explore innovative methods to engage with your favorite content, people, and entertainment. Windows 11 Home becomes your natural canvas for thinking, expressing, and creating.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Laptop for the price, I think you'll be pretty satisfied
reviews.reviewText: I've had this computer for just a couple of days so far and I can say it's pretty great so far. It's slim and lightweight. Great processing power and great graphics. Runs low end games relatively well, but do note it's not a gaming computer if that's what your looking for. The only thing I will say is I'm not a fan of the integrated battery, and if you do play your games on it or something else pretty power intensive it will drain the battery insanely fast, but it charges fast too. I'd recommend keeping it plugged in if you decide to run a game, but all other activities--searching the web, typing documents, etc--it's totally fine. I'd definitely recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice value priced laptop
reviews.reviewText: Pretty fast laptop, boots up in about 30 seconds when restarted, instant on otherwise.Non glare display could be brighter but is pretty good when set @ High Contrast...Backlit keyboard seems quite nice, fingerprint reader works great.Battery life seems a bit limited, but does recharge very quickly.Only issue common to all PC's is the Windows based operating system,ya think after 30 years of trying Bill Gates could make A decent glitch free operating system!Wish I could have afforded a Mac, Still prefer my 4 year old ipad 90% of time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Performance for Money
reviews.reviewText: I was getting a laptop for college and I needed something that I would be able to do CAD on (at least a moderate amount with decent performance) and all other laptops in this range did not offer nearly the specs this one did. The ryzen cpu, and 8gigs (technically 6 since 2 are dedicated to the iGPU) are all fast and having the gtx 1050 for dedicated graphics perfectly fits my needs. Also, it comes with a 512gb SSD, something no other laptop in the price range offered. The catch all to all of these is that the battery is pretty bad. The only way for the system to use the dedicated graphics card is if it is plugged in, at least if you want to use it for more than an hour. However, using it in low power mode off the charger for basic things like web browsing, studying, and watching Youtube the battery lasts several hours. The charger itself isn't too big either so it is not a pain to carry around. I recommend this if you are looking for performance per dollar and don't mind carrying around your charger.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love my laptop
reviews.reviewText: I just fell in love with this laptop. My husband is my own personal tech so to his eyes this was a great buy. It was worth the wait and the time I had to save to finally get a new laptop after 10 years of using one that was a gift.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great hardware specs, but bad sale
reviews.reviewText: This laptop came in great condition. However, as another reviewer noted, it didn't come with the mouse like it was supposed to.The monitor is not a high DPI despite its high resolution, due to the fact that the monitor is quite large. I'm still deciding how important that is to me - if it is, I might return the laptop.This laptop also came with S mode enabled on W11 Home, which again was not described anywhere and is insurmountably annoying because you can't run any executables other than Microsoft Store apps. If you don't want to connect your MS account to Windows (which MS pushes so hard, but is not a great idea for a number of reasons), you have to reinstall Windows to disable S mode.The keyboard also looks and feels like something lifted off a cheap HP laptop from 6 years ago. Overall, it does the job, but it's not impressive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Exelente producto por el valor pagado, el envio internacional (especificamente colombia) muy rapido, menos de una semana. El producto llego en exelentes condiciones, exelente calidad de construccion, rendimiento espectacular, la calidad de la pantalla es promedio, el trackpad es bastante bueno por este valor, el teclado esta bastante bien aunque considerar que tiene distribucion estado unidense, buena retroiluminacion, los altavoces y la abteria son los puntos debiles ya que la bateria promedia unas 4 horas de trabajo basico, maximo 5 en modo ahorro y exigiendole no pasa de 1 hora, por ultimo el peso es considerable, pero para su segmento es bastante delgado, perfectamente llevable en el dia a dia.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Did not come with mouse as shown in picture

reviews.reviewText: Yo la compré para uso escolar y para gaming, en ambas es una excelente opción, corre juegos como The Witcher 3 y GTA V con gráficos en ultra y vale la pena el precio totalmente

I'm a digital artist / small time gamer. This laptop has beyond exceeded my expectations.I'm used to running games, such as 7DTD, Sims, Don't Starve, etc, on the lowest possible settings. This laptop? Auto sets them to high, or fantastic quality, and runs them without a single issue. 7DTD, Ark, L4D2, and My Time At Portia, all run on high or better quality.Battery life? Excellent. Storage space? Great, SSD is awesome, but plan to add a harddrive for extra space. Dedicated drivers? AWESOME. Runs everything so smoothly. Price? Completely justified. I was hesitant to spend this much money on a new laptop, when I could find a lesser model for 200$ less, but this was definitely a much better decision.
Estoy muy satisfecho con la compra excelente relación calidad precio, me va muy bien con visual studio y también la he probado con lol y fall guys y me va sin problemas
No sirve se sobrecalienta y se apaga al estar simplemente viendo videos

reviews.reviewTitle: Good cheap machine, bit low on ram
reviews.reviewText: Bought the 8gb version of this and it ran pretty bad on games I play (Rust for instance), upgraded to 32 gb now it's a beast for the price. Don't expect to run newer games at full detail, but definitely good enough to enjoy stuff. It's fairly quiet despite others saying it was really loud.It was a major pain in the arse to upgrade the ram, literally had to remove every single screw and part to get to the memory bank.There's a spot in there for a second hard drive too (I have 1 ssd version).Paid 750 cnd which is a total steal for the power it has.
